                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.86,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 68169,
                                "text": "I have the opinion of the Court to announce in No. 03 101, Norton Versus Southern Utah Wilderness Alliance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 9.86,
                                "stop": 14.834,
                                "byte_start": 68169,
                                "byte_stop": 88022,
                                "text": "The case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the Court of Appeals for the Tenth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.834,
                                "stop": 24.216,
                                "byte_start": 88022,
                                "byte_stop": 125639,
                                "text": "Almost half of the State of Utah\u2019s federal land administered by the Bureau of Land Management or BLM, an agency within the Department of the Interior."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.216,
                                "stop": 29.243,
                                "byte_start": 125639,
                                "byte_stop": 145701,
                                "text": "This case involves lands which may in the future be designated as Wilderness areas."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.243,
                                "stop": 40.011,
                                "byte_start": 145701,
                                "byte_stop": 188750,
                                "text": "The respondent of Southern Utah Wilderness Alliance sued the Bureau of Land Management, claiming that they had failed to protect these lands from damage by off road vehicles."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.011,
                                "stop": 43.466,
                                "byte_start": 188750,
                                "byte_stop": 202543,
                                "text": "The District Court dismissed all three of respondent\u2019s claims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 43.466,
                                "stop": 48.17,
                                "byte_start": 202543,
                                "byte_stop": 221456,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals reversed and we granted certiorari."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.17,
                                "stop": 56.502,
                                "byte_start": 221456,
                                "byte_stop": 254683,
                                "text": "Respondent\u2019s first claim is that the BLM failed to protect Wilderness study areas from off road vehicle use."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.502,
                                "stop": 75.236,
                                "byte_start": 254683,
                                "byte_stop": 329707,
                                "text": "A violation of the requirement in a law called the Federal Land Policy Management Act, which I shall hereafter refer to as FLPMA, that BLM mismanaged Wilderness study areas so as not to impair their suitability for preservation as Wilderness."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.236,
                                "stop": 91.08,
                                "byte_start": 329707,
                                "byte_stop": 393028,
                                "text": "However, both the text of the APA and Pre-APA mandamus practice make it clear, that such a claim can proceed only where a plaintiff asserts that an agency fails to make a discrete agency action that is required to take."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.08,
                                "stop": 106.311,
                                "byte_start": 393028,
                                "byte_stop": 453945,
                                "text": "The discrete-action limitation precludes broad programmatic attacks and the required action limitation rules out judicial direction of even discrete agency action that is not demanded by law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.311,
                                "stop": 119.675,
                                "byte_start": 453945,
                                "byte_stop": 507444,
                                "text": "Applying these principles to the present claim, FLPMA\u2019s non-impairment mandate is mandatory as to the object to be achieved; it leaves the Bureau of Land Management discretion to decide how to achieve that object."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.675,
                                "stop": 126.249,
                                "byte_start": 507444,
                                "byte_stop": 533671,
                                "text": "The second claim is that the BLM failed to comply with the provisions of its own land use plans."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.249,
                                "stop": 135.193,
                                "byte_start": 533671,
                                "byte_stop": 569511,
                                "text": "A land use plan however is a tool to project present and future use, just one step in the overall process of managing public land."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.193,
                                "stop": 143.244,
                                "byte_start": 569511,
                                "byte_stop": 601694,
                                "text": "Unlike a specific statutory command require an agency too, for example, promulgate regulations by a certain day."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.244,
                                "stop": 149.465,
                                "byte_start": 601694,
                                "byte_stop": 626563,
                                "text": "A land use plan guides and restrains actions, but in general does not prescribe them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 149.465,
                                "stop": 158.541,
                                "byte_start": 626563,
                                "byte_stop": 662925,
                                "text": "The land use plan statement at issue here are not a legally binding commitment enforceable under Section 706."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.541,
                                "stop": 179.582,
                                "byte_start": 662925,
                                "byte_stop": 747039,
                                "text": "We also reject respondent\u2019s third contention regarding BLM\u2019s fulfillment of purported obligations under NEPA, the National Environment Policy Act, to take a so-called hard look at whether it must supplement certain of its environmental impact statements in light of evidence of increased off road vehicle use."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.582,
                                "stop": 196.883,
                                "byte_start": 747039,
                                "byte_stop": 816212,
                                "text": "To make a long story short, we find that those obligations attached only to proposed or yet to be completed actions and that the Bureau\u2019s land use plans, once approved, are completed actions, giving rise to no further supplemental obligations under NEPA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.883,
                                "stop": 203.212,
                                "byte_start": 816212,
                                "byte_stop": 841603,
                                "text": "For these reasons and others discussed in an opinion authored by Justice Scalia and filed with the Clerk today."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 203.212,
                                "stop": 210.297,
                                "byte_start": 841603,
                                "byte_stop": 869919,
                                "text": "We hold that none of the three alleged failures to act can be enforced by means of a suit under 7061."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 210.297,
                                "stop": 233.735,
                                "byte_start": 869919,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "So, the judgment of the Court of Appeals is reversed and the decision of the Court in unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
